    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 lb boneless, skinless chicken thighs, cut into bite-sized pieces</li>
            <li>1 cup plain yogurt</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon garam masala</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon ground cumin</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon ground coriander</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon turmeric powder</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon chili powder (adjust to taste)</li>
            <li>Salt, to taste</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons vegetable oil</li>
            <li>1 large onion, finely chopped</li>
            <li>1 can (14 oz) tomato sauce</li>
            <li>1 cup heavy cream</li>
            <li>1/4 cup chopped fresh cilantro, for garnish</li>
            <li>Cooked basmati rice, for serving</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a bowl, combine yogurt, ginger-garlic paste, garam masala, cumin, coriander, turmeric, chili powder, and salt. Add the chicken pieces, making sure they are well-coated. Marinate for at least 1 hour or overnight in the refrigerator.</li>
            <li>Heat vegetable oil in a skillet over medium heat. Add chopped onions and saut√© until golden brown.</li>
            <li>Add the marinated chicken to the skillet and cook until browned on all sides.</li>
            <li>Stir in tomato sauce and simmer for 15-20 minutes, allowing the flavors to meld and the chicken to cook through.</li>
            <li>Pour in heavy cream, stir well, and let it simmer for an additional 5 minutes.</li>
            <li>Garnish with chopped cilantro and serve the Chicken Tikka Masala over cooked basmati rice.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your flavorful Chicken Tikka Masala!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

